com.github.dm.jrt.android.reflect.builder

Interface LoaderReflectionRoutineBuilder

  • All Superinterfaces:
    InvocationConfigurable<ReflectionRoutineBuilder>, InvocationConfiguration.Configurable<ReflectionRoutineBuilder>, LoaderConfigurable<LoaderReflectionRoutineBuilder>, LoaderConfiguration.Configurable<LoaderReflectionRoutineBuilder>, ReflectionConfigurable<ReflectionRoutineBuilder>, ReflectionConfiguration.Configurable<ReflectionRoutineBuilder>, ReflectionRoutineBuilder

    public interface LoaderReflectionRoutineBuilder
extends ReflectionRoutineBuilder, LoaderConfigurable<LoaderReflectionRoutineBuilder>
    Interface defining a builder of routines wrapping an object methods.

    The single methods can be accessed via reflection or the whole instance can be proxied through an interface.

    Created by davide-maestroni on 04/06/2015.

      • buildProxy

        @NotNull
<TYPE> TYPE buildProxy(@NotNull
                                Class<TYPE> itf)
        Returns a proxy object enabling asynchronous call of the target instance methods.

        The routines used for calling the methods will honor the attributes specified in any optional com.github.dm.jrt.reflect.annotation.* as well as com.github.dm.jrt.android.reflect.annotation.* annotations.
        Note that such annotations will override any configuration set through the builder.

        Specified by:
        buildProxy in interface ReflectionRoutineBuilder
        Type Parameters:
        TYPE - the interface type.
        Parameters:
        itf - the token of the interface implemented by the return object.
        Returns:
        the proxy object.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified class does not represent an interface.

      • method

        @NotNull
<IN,OUT> LoaderRoutine<IN,OUT> method(@NotNull
                                               String name)
        Returns a routine used to call the method whose identifying name is specified in an Alias annotation.

        If no method with the specified alias is found, this method will behave like method(String, Class[]) with no parameter.
        Optional com.github.dm.jrt.reflect.annotation.* as well as com.github.dm.jrt.android.reflect.annotation.* method annotations will be honored.
        Note that such annotations will override any configuration set through the builder.

        Specified by:
        method in interface ReflectionRoutineBuilder
        Type Parameters:
        IN - the input data type.
        OUT - the output data type.
        Parameters:
        name - the name specified in the annotation.
        Returns:
        the routine.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified method is not found.
        See Also:
        Android Annotations, Annotations

      • method

        @NotNull
<IN,OUT> LoaderRoutine<IN,OUT> method(@NotNull
                                               String name,
                                               @NotNull
                                               Class<?>... parameterTypes)
        Returns a routine used to call the specified method.

        The method is searched via reflection ignoring a name specified in an Alias annotation. Though, optional com.github.dm.jrt.reflect.annotation.* as well as com.github.dm.jrt.android.reflect.annotation.* method annotations will be honored.
        Note that such annotations will override any configuration set through the builder.

        Specified by:

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        the routine.
        Throws:
